## Required Patterns

The agent generates or reminds the user to add these for every new feature:

- **Validator co-location:** Every command/query has a `CommandNameValidator.cs`
  in the same folder as the handler
- **Handler unit test:** Every handler has a corresponding test in `*.UnitTests`
- **Endpoint integration test:** Every new endpoint has a test in `*.IntegrationTests`
- **Architecture boundary test:** `*.ArchitectureTests` project runs in CI with
  `NetArchTest` rules enforcing all layer boundaries above

---

## Violations

### ❌ Violation 1 — Repository interface defined in Infrastructure

**Trigger:** Agent generates `ProductRepository` with the interface and
implementation in the same `Infrastructure/Persistence/` folder.

**What to flag:**
> The `IProductRepository` interface must live in
> `Application/Interfaces/IProductRepository.cs` (or `Domain/Interfaces/`),
> not in `Infrastructure`. The Infrastructure project depends on Application,
> not the other way around. Move the interface — the implementation stays in Infrastructure.

---

### ❌ Violation 2 — Controller action contains conditional business logic

**Trigger:** PR adds a 40-line controller action with if-statements determining
order eligibility, discount calculation, and tax rounding.

**What to flag:**
> Controllers are transport adapters — they map HTTP to MediatR and back.
> All the logic in lines 15–55 belongs in a `CalculateOrderTotalsCommand`
> handler in the Application layer, where it can be unit-tested without
> spinning up an HTTP server. Refactor: extract to handler, controller becomes
> 8 lines.
